COUNT OF A:

public class Vowels
{
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		String a="balasubramaniyan";
		int count=0;
		int countOfa=0;
		for(int i=0; i<a.length(); i++) {
			char ch=a.charAt(i);
			switch(ch) {
			case 'a':countOfa++;break;
			case 'e':count++;break;
			case 'i':count++;break;
			case 'o':count++;break;
			case 'u':count++;break;
    }
		}
		System.out.println("count of 'a' in the given string is: "+countOfa);
		System.out.println("count of vowels in the given string is: "+count);
	
	}
}

OUTPUT:
    count of 'a' in the given string is: 5
    count of vowels in the given string is: 2
